</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8438A9FE9B5010FC0256229A99A0E2E8" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="619246AFD0AE562749D6B428F95A0910" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="636FF7665C31983183A42D06E4D6C684" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
The generic name is derived from the Greek &quot; 
<emphasis id="0060C2EA0D1FE2AA05A9E49B2FCED776" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">nothos</emphasis>
&quot;, false, and the generic name 
<taxonomicName id="552AE34DB3C765EFC33AFB5D58C14E1C" authorityName="Le Conte" authorityYear="1851" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Tytthonyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tytthonyx" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="AED634CD68DFEE0FCA2FBBA1C927B99E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Tytthonyx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
LeConte. The name is masculine in gender.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0F32CE0853612FF03D21B637B307FBB3" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="3CA852AC6624548424C2013C5B9FCF74" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9A10A5AD20058C1886059508A27F13C3" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
Antennae strongly serrate (Figs 
<figureCitation id="162C29A0F4FFA2AE916F1CE6E2575D79" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Details of Nothotytthonyx serratus Li, Biffi, Kundrata &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP 179427, under confocal microscopy A head, ventral view, showing the confluent gular suture (arrowhead) B prothorax, ventral view C metathorax, ventral view D abdominal base, ventral view E abdominal apex, ventral view F head, dorsal view G prothorax, dorsal view H elytral base, dorsal view H abdominal apex, dorsal view. Abbreviations: an 1 - 11, antennomeres 1 - 11; el, elytron; ey, compound eye; md, mandible; msf, mesofemur; mtc, metacoxa; mttb, metatibia; mtts, metatarsus; mtv, metaventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; pc, procoxa; pn, pronotum; ps, prosternum; v 1 - 7, ventrites 1 - 7. Scale bars: 300 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.81701.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667939" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">3F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="A421951C36B6ED4EF9D18CFFC3B111A9" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Details of Nothotytthonyx serratus Li, Biffi, Kundrata &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP 179427, under confocal microscopy A mouthparts, ventral view B antennal base, dorsal view C antennal apex D mid leg, showing the two weak tibial spurs (arrowhead) E abdominal apex, dorsal view F ovipositor, ventral view. Abbreviations: an 1 - 11, antennomeres 1 - 11; gc, gonocoxite; gs, gonostylus; lbp, labial palp; mst 1 - 5, mesotarsomeres 1 - 5; mstb, mesotibia; mxp, maxillary palp. Scale bars: 200 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.81701.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667940" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">4C</figureCitation>
). Mandibles with a prominent tooth on incisor edge (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F2294FA18077170A2653AABC5BC59FD2" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. X-ray microtomographic reconstruction of Nothotytthonyx serratus Li, Biffi, Kundrata &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP 179427 A dorsal view B ventral view C lateral view D anterodorsal view E anterolateral view. Scale bar: 2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.81701.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667941" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">5D</figureCitation>
). Apical maxillary palpomere symmetrical, fusiform (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="52FFF1FB0F187E2D2A4036925CD85DFA" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Details of Nothotytthonyx serratus Li, Biffi, Kundrata &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP 179427, under confocal microscopy A mouthparts, ventral view B antennal base, dorsal view C antennal apex D mid leg, showing the two weak tibial spurs (arrowhead) E abdominal apex, dorsal view F ovipositor, ventral view. Abbreviations: an 1 - 11, antennomeres 1 - 11; gc, gonocoxite; gs, gonostylus; lbp, labial palp; mst 1 - 5, mesotarsomeres 1 - 5; mstb, mesotibia; mxp, maxillary palp. Scale bars: 200 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.81701.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667940" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">4A</figureCitation>
). Gular sutures confluent (Figs 
<figureCitation id="FC7C341FECD5E9CF12BC6E4E76BAD13E" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Details of Nothotytthonyx serratus Li, Biffi, Kundrata &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP 179427, under confocal microscopy A head, ventral view, showing the confluent gular suture (arrowhead) B prothorax, ventral view C metathorax, ventral view D abdominal base, ventral view E abdominal apex, ventral view F head, dorsal view G prothorax, dorsal view H elytral base, dorsal view H abdominal apex, dorsal view. Abbreviations: an 1 - 11, antennomeres 1 - 11; el, elytron; ey, compound eye; md, mandible; msf, mesofemur; mtc, metacoxa; mttb, metatibia; mtts, metatarsus; mtv, metaventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; pc, procoxa; pn, pronotum; ps, prosternum; v 1 - 7, ventrites 1 - 7. Scale bars: 300 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.81701.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667939" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">3A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="D3161EA6105E665843BCAF41716C5753" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. X-ray microtomographic reconstruction of Nothotytthonyx serratus Li, Biffi, Kundrata &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP 179427 A dorsal view B ventral view C lateral view D anterodorsal view E anterolateral view. Scale bar: 2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.81701.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667941" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">5B</figureCitation>
). Elytra shortened; surface somewhat punctate. Tibial spurs present (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="77532A5E6DAEA5A8AECAD7C81EFD57FB" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Details of Nothotytthonyx serratus Li, Biffi, Kundrata &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP 179427, under confocal microscopy A mouthparts, ventral view B antennal base, dorsal view C antennal apex D mid leg, showing the two weak tibial spurs (arrowhead) E abdominal apex, dorsal view F ovipositor, ventral view. Abbreviations: an 1 - 11, antennomeres 1 - 11; gc, gonocoxite; gs, gonostylus; lbp, labial palp; mst 1 - 5, mesotarsomeres 1 - 5; mstb, mesotibia; mxp, maxillary palp. Scale bars: 200 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.81701.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667940" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">4D</figureCitation>
). Gonostyli well developed (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="2F4914A97E6F55F8A790A816FD155F7D" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Details of Nothotytthonyx serratus Li, Biffi, Kundrata &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP 179427, under confocal microscopy A mouthparts, ventral view B antennal base, dorsal view C antennal apex D mid leg, showing the two weak tibial spurs (arrowhead) E abdominal apex, dorsal view F ovipositor, ventral view. Abbreviations: an 1 - 11, antennomeres 1 - 11; gc, gonocoxite; gs, gonostylus; lbp, labial palp; mst 1 - 5, mesotarsomeres 1 - 5; mstb, mesotibia; mxp, maxillary palp. Scale bars: 200 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.81701.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667940" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">4F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
